---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";

const title = "AWS cost checklist: a simple budgeting framework";
const description =
  "A practical AWS cost checklist to build a realistic monthly budget: compute, storage, data transfer, observability, and CDN - plus validation steps to avoid surprises.";
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why do AWS budgets miss?",
    a: "They model only compute. The biggest misses are transfer (egress/cross-AZ), logs/metrics, and request-priced services that scale with traffic.",
  },
  {
    q: "What is the fastest way to get a baseline number?",
    a: "Use a blended rate approach: estimate the monthly drivers (hours, GB-month, requests, GB/month transfer), multiply by effective unit prices, then refine for tiering and region mix later.",
  },
  {
    q: "How should I validate the checklist estimate?",
    a: "Compare directionality against a real week of metrics or billing exports. Validate units (GB vs GiB) and separate CDN bandwidth from origin egress.",
  },
];
---
<GuideLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/guides/aws-cost-checklist"
  lastUpdated="2026-01-22"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p class="muted">
    Use this checklist when you want a "good enough" AWS budget quickly. The goal is to avoid missing the line items
    that most often surprise teams.
  </p>

  <h2>1) Compute</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/calculators/ec2-cost-calculator/">EC2 cost</a> (instances x $/hour x hours/month x uptime)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/calculators/eks-cost-calculator/">EKS cost</a> (nodes + control plane) and{" "}
      <a href="/guides/aws-eks-control-plane-cost/">control plane guide</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2) Storage</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/calculators/s3-cost-calculator/">S3 cost</a> (storage + requests + egress)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/calculators/s3-request-cost-calculator/">S3 request cost</a> and{" "}
      <a href="/guides/aws-s3-request-costs/">request cost guide</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="/calculators/s3-replication-cost-calculator/">S3 replication</a> (if you replicate/copy data)
    </li>
    <li>
      Storage classes and archive: <a href="/guides/aws-s3-storage-classes/">storage classes</a> and{" "}
      <a href="/calculators/aws-s3-glacier-cost-calculator/">archive cost calculator</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3) Data transfer (usually the biggest surprise)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/calculators/vpc-data-transfer-cost-calculator/">VPC transfer</a></li>
    <li><a href="/calculators/data-egress-cost-calculator/">Internet egress</a></li>
    <li>
      Guide: <a href="/guides/network-transfer-costs/">network transfer costs explained</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4) Observability</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/calculators/log-cost-calculator/">Log cost</a></li>
    <li><a href="/calculators/log-search-scan-cost-calculator/">Log search/scan</a></li>
    <li><a href="/calculators/metrics-timeseries-cost-calculator/">Metrics series cost</a></li>
    <li>
      Guide: <a href="/guides/aws-logging-cost-reduction/">reduce logging costs</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5) CDN</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/calculators/cloudfront-cost-calculator/">CloudFront cost</a></li>
    <li>
      Guide: <a href="/guides/cdn-costs/">CDN costs explained</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Validation checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Validate units: GB vs GiB and request units (per 10k vs per 1M).</li>
    <li>Separate CDN bandwidth (edge-to-user) from origin egress (cache fill).</li>
    <li>Re-check incident windows: retries/timeouts can multiply requests and transfer.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Related reading</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/cloud-cost-estimation-checklist/">Full cost estimation checklist</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/aws-ec2-cost-estimation/">EC2 estimation</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/aws-s3-data-transfer/">S3 transfer</a>
    <a class="btn" href="/guides/aws-logging-cost-reduction/">Reduce logging costs</a>
  </div>
</GuideLayout>

